<div class="section_title">Behind the Scenes</div>
<span class="text">
Check out Behind the Scenes at CES for updates on the extra efforts the International CES makes to create a positive show experience for you.
<P><A href="#" name=scene1></A><STRONG>Quick Resolution of Local 631 Teamsters Strike Means Business as Usual in Las Vegas</STRONG><BR>Recent news from Las Vegas is that the Teamsters Local 631 has agreed to a new three-year agreement with convention service contractors, GES Exposition Services and the Freeman Companies.&nbsp; The agreement ensures the continuation of appropriate levels of labor for the Las Vegas convention industry, which is good news for CES and our exhibitors. Questions? Please contact Dawn Rhine, Show Director, International CES, (703) 907-7651 and <A href="mailto:drhine@CE.org">drhine@CE.org</A>. </P>
<P><A href="#" name=scene2></A><STRONG>Exhibitor Registration is Live</STRONG><BR>We’ve streamlined our exhibitor and international delegation registration system, and now you can sign your booth staff and delegation members up <A href="/print/exhibitors/resource_center/badges/default.asp">online</A>.</P>
<P><A href="#" name=scene3></A><STRONG>Exhibitor Appointed Contractors: New Online Registrations</STRONG><BR>CES is happy to introduce a new online registration tool for Exhibitor Appointed Contractors (EAC).</P>
<P>The tool, set to launch September 20, 2004, will allow you to register your EAC at www.CESweb.org/MyEAC. Your EAC will then be able to manage show information, sign off on EAC agreements and submit certificates of insurance at www.CESweb.org/EAC, a site that will also launch on September 20, 2004.</P>
<P>This new tool saves time and paperwork and makes exhibiting at the International CES easier. </P>
<P><STRONG><A href="#" name=scene4></A>Renaissance Hotel Suites Available</STRONG><BR>Whether you’ve got an important meeting to host or you’re looking for exclusive hospitality space, we’ve been able to secure additional space at the new Renaissance Las Vegas Hotel.</P>
<P><A href="/print/docs/RenaissanceSuitesFlyer.pdf" target=_blank>The Renaissance Las Vegas Hotel opportunity (pdf)</A> gives CES exhibitors a chance to host an event at this exclusive, brand new facility—at CES rates!</P>
<P>If you really want to impress clients and buyers, the Renaissance Las Vegas Hotel offers a superior location, contemporary design and high-tech amenities. Exhibitor suites and deluxe suites are available at member and non-member rates in this sophisticated, energizing atmosphere. The suites are for meeting and hospitality purposes only, as we cannot accommodate exhibiting products there.</P>
<P>Plus, the Renaissance Las Vegas Hotel is&nbsp;adjacent to&nbsp;the new Las Vegas monorail, with a stop at the Las Vegas Convention Center.</P>For more information, please contact Scott Kromer at (703) 907-7020 or <A href="mailto:skromer@CE.org">skromer@CE.org</A>.
</span>
