<div class="section_title">Free Exposure for Your Products</div>
<span class="text">
<IMG height=80 hspace=6 src="/print/images/general/techgirl75.gif" width=75 align=right>Not all women prefer diamonds. If your products have what it takes to wow the tech-savvy female consumer electronics market, they could be selected to be featured in the <A href="/print/attendees/awards/techgirl/default.asp">Technology is a Girl’s Best Friend Product Showcase</A>&nbsp;at the 2005 International CES. 
<P>
<P>Women today are buying the latest electronics to the tune of $55 billion per year. If your products appeal to this influential buyer market, enter them in the <A href="/print/exhibitors/newsletter/submission.asp">product showcase</A>. </P>
<P>Submit your products to be judged by a preeminent panel of technology and style journalists. Winning products earn a special spot at the 2005 International CES, January 6-9 in Las Vegas, Nevada.&nbsp; <BR>Judges will evaluate the product’s form, function, usability, and ability to enhance women’s lifestyles. If your product is selected, it will be featured in the highly-trafficked Tech Girl Product Showcase in the CES Store, LVCC Grand Lobby. </P>
<P>Product categories include: 
<UL>
<LI>Audio </LI>
<LI>Computer/IT </LI>
<LI>Electronic Gaming </LI>
<LI>Digital Imaging </LI>
<LI>Home Networking </LI>
<LI>Mobile Electronics </LI>
<LI>Video </LI>
<LI>Wireless</LI></UL><BR>The Product Showcase is one component of a comprehensive, year-round CEA program focusing on the female technology consumer. <BR><BR>Entries accepted until 5 p.m. EST September 30, 2004. <A href="/print/exhibitors/newsletter/submission.asp">Enter online</A>. <BR><BR>Questions? Contact <A href="mailto:TechGirl@CE.org">TechGirl@CE.org</A>.
</span>
