    <p><strong>United We Stand</strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    The U.S. has the largest and most technologically powerful economy in the world. I recently read this (and the statistics to back it up) on the CIA website, and of course, I was impressed and proud to be a part of it. 
<P>Each of the 50 states contributes in some way to the nation’s success. They flourish separately in their own areas of expertise, but come together as a whole to make our nation successful. </P>
<P>Forever in search of a good analogy, I instantly drew a parallel: The <A href="/print/exhibitors/space/techzones.asp">International CES TechZones</A>&nbsp;are just like states. These zones each demonstrate their own expertise. While they’re distinctly different, they collectively represent, demonstrate and contribute to the power and growth of the consumer technology industry as a whole. Combined with the other aspects of the International CES, TechZones help create the largest annual consumer technology event. </P>
<P>I don’t plan on quizzing you like your fourth grade teacher did during social studies, but please take a minute to get to know your tradeshow’s states—the International CES TechZones. And while you do, remember that opportunities still exist in many of these for you. So if they correspond with your business, <A href="/print/exhibitors/space/contacts.asp">please contact one of us</A>&nbsp;to find out how you can participate.&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>
